name: PerformanceMark
description: PerformanceMark is an abstract interface for performance entries with an entry type of "mark". Entries of this type are created by calling performance.mark() to add a named DOMHighResTimeStamp (the mark) to the browser's performance timeline.

members.name: PerformanceEntry.name
members.description: Set to the the name given to the mark when it was created via a call to performance.mark().

members.name: PerformanceEntry.startTime
members.description: Set to the DOMHighResTimeStamp when performance.mark() was called.

members.name: PerformanceEntry.duration
members.description: Set to "0" (a mark has no duration).
